🧭 0. System Overview

Goal:

Detect IR LEDs → match to known 3D layout → estimate pose → optionally triangulate

Pipeline:

Image → Blob Detection → Blob Filtering → Matching → Pose Estimation (PnP)
      → Temporal Tracking (IMU fusion) → (Optional) Triangulation

🔍 1. LED Detection (Blob Detection)

Minimal:
1. Convert image → grayscale (or IR channel)
2. Apply threshold
3. Find connected components
4. Extract:
      * centroid (x, y)
      * area

👉 This already works in controlled environments

Optimal:
1. Adaptive threshold (per frame or region)
2. Handle:
    * merged blobs (split using shape heuristics)
    * faint blobs (lower threshold + filtering)
3. Use multi-scale detection:
    image pyramid → detect blobs at different scales
4. Subpixel centroid estimation

👉 Inspired by:

* blob segmentation improvements
* pyramid-based detection

🧹 2. Blob Filtering (Outlier Rejection)
Minimal
Filter by:
min/max area
brightness threshold

👉 Removes obvious noise

Optimal

Two-stage filtering:

A. Geometric / temporal filtering
Track blobs across frames
Identify stationary blobs
Build 3D map (triangulate over time)
Remove them in future frames

👉 Removes:

lights, reflections, background clutter
B. Learned / physical filtering
Validate blob size using:
distance estimate
viewing angle
Option:
small classifier (e.g., lightweight CNN)

👉 Removes:

physically inconsistent blobs


🔗 3. Matching (2D blobs ↔ 3D LEDs)
Minimal
Assume:
small number of blobs
known LED layout

Approach:

brute-force assign correspondences
try all combinations (small N)
run PnP → pick lowest reprojection error

👉 Works if:

few blobs
low ambiguity
Optimal
A. Two matching modes
1. Brute matching
used when:
no prior pose
enumerate hypotheses
2. Proximity matching
use previous pose
project 3D LEDs → image
search only nearby blobs

👉 Much faster and more stable

B. Multi-camera matching
combine observations across cameras
enforce geometric consistency

👉 Important when:

each camera sees few LEDs
C. Hypothesis + validation (RANSAC-style)
pick minimal matches → generate pose
validate with remaining blobs
choose best hypothesis
📐 4. Pose Estimation (PnP)
Minimal

Use standard Perspective-n-Point (PnP) problem:

OpenCV solvePnP
Require ≥4 matches
Optimal
A. Multiple solvers
Full PnP (≥4 points)
P3P (minimal)
Reduced solvers:
P2P (use prior orientation)
P1P (strong prior)

👉 Enables tracking with:

1–3 LEDs visible
B. Use priors
initialize with previous pose
constrain optimization
C. Robust optimization
minimize reprojection error
reject outliers (RANSAC / M-estimators)
🔁 5. Temporal Tracking (Filtering + IMU Fusion)
Minimal
Use previous pose as initialization
simple smoothing (moving average)
Optimal
A. IMU fusion
combine:
camera pose
IMU (gyro + accel)
e.g.:
Extended Kalman Filter (EKF)
B. Prediction
predict pose when LEDs missing
reduces need for brute matching
C. State machine

Switch modes:

good tracking → fast methods
lost tracking → brute recovery
📍 6. Triangulation (if multi-view / multi-frame)
Minimal
If 2+ cameras:
match same LED across views
triangulate via ray intersection
Optimal
A. Multi-view triangulation
use all cameras jointly
least squares solution
B. Temporal triangulation
accumulate observations over time
refine LED positions or landmarks
C. Use for:
mapping environment (SLAM-style)
filtering static lights
⚡ 7. Performance Optimization
Minimal
process every frame equally
Optimal
adaptive compute:
skip heavy steps when confident
enable pyramids only when needed
ROI-based processing
parallelize per camera
